@ Before start handling of BTPC rows for one client, the CMON row (s) have to
be locked, because of deadlock problems --> CMON/CMOC
BPH260 perfrom updates on CMON/CMOC in sequence 1. CMOC and then
2. CMON, related to the SORT of BTPC rows, but all other programs will update
in sequence 1. CMON and then 2. CMOC, which occures the deadlock, if multiple
programs tries to update the same CMON/CMOC rows
INFO: The lock on CMON for the current selected client (=BTPC_CLNTNO) will be
unlocked according to the transaction level, means if all BTPC rows
are handled for one client

SQL_STMT_U.val: SELECT BTCH_DATE, CAST(SUM(BTPC_MUTAFACTORING) as decimal (18,2)), CAST(SUM(BTPC_MUTASETTLEMENT) as decimal (18,2)), CAST(SUM(BTPC_MUTARETENTION) as decimal (18,2)), CAST(SUM(BTPC_MUTADISPUTES) as decimal (18,2)), CAST(SUM(BTPC_MUTASPECIAL) as decimal (18,2)), CAST(SUM(BTPC_MUTAEXTFIN) as decimal (18,2)) FROM :1/btpc, :1/btch WHERE :4 BTPC_ADMNO = :2 and BTPC_CLNTNO= :3 and BTPC_STATUS = 2 AND BTCH_ID=BTPC_BTCH_ID GROUP BY BTCH_DATE ORDER BY BTCH_DATE FOR FETCH ONLY OPTIMIZE FOR 100 ROWS
